本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:翁漱璞研究生(外文):Su-Pu Weng論文名稱:華山創意文化園區周邊都市空間規劃策略之研究論文名稱(外文):The Research for Planning Strategy on Surrounding Urban Space of the Huashan Creative and Cultural Park指導教授:蘇瑛敏學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立臺北科技大學系所名稱:建築與都市設計研究所學門:建築及都市規劃學門學類:建築學類論文出版年:2008畢業學年度:97語文別:中文論文頁數:150中文關鍵詞:華山創意文化園區、文化創意產業、都市空間規劃策略外文關鍵詞:Huashan Creative and Cultural Park、Creative and Cultural industries、Urban Space Planning Strategy相關次數:

被引用:16點閱:1077評分:下載:0書目收藏:5



邁向21世紀，世界各國城市在面對全球化影響下，開始將文化產業概念引用於都市與區域政策，發展文化產業策略來推動都市再生，及地方經濟發展，以提昇自身的競爭力。台灣政府繼閒置空間再利用、地方文化館等文化與空間政策之後，文建會將全台五大酒廠舊址，規劃為創意文化園區。但回顧近十年所推動的文化政策，發現許多案例在規劃時僅針對單一據點內的硬體再生、活動舉辦等面向思考，並未顧及都市周邊產業及空間結構的連結，無法有效整合地區整體資源，對都市發展的波及效果有限。再加上缺乏相關法令調整的情形下，難以有效的推動再利用計畫，常演變為無法扮演融入周邊社區生活文化及缺乏長期經濟支持的藝文空間。本研究首先回顧各國文化創意產業之定義、發展、聚集過程與都市發展的關係等相關文獻，探討台灣創意文化園區的定位及發展目標。第二階段回顧台灣文化產業發展歷程及現況調查分析，探討園區與都市發展及周邊空間的課題。第三階段蒐集並分析探討國外相關案例，歸納華山創意文化園區發展值得借鏡之處。最後，綜合上述小結並以創意城市、都市文化觀光、文化生活圈等，人文創意環境取向的都市空間創新規劃觀點，提出華山創意文化園區周圍都市空間的發展策略及建議，以塑造都市文化特殊性及營造空間的創意氛圍，做為發展文化創意產業群聚的基礎，進而帶動城市產業群的蓬勃發展，達到不斷更新及創新的目標。

Toward the 21st century, cities around the world, under the influence of globalization, have begun to apply concept of cultural industry to urban and regional industry, develop cultural industry strategy for urban revitalization and local economic development in order to strengthen their competence.After the cultural and spatial policies such as Adaptive Reuse of Deserted Space and Local Cultural Museum, the Council for Cultural Affairs designed five former brewery sites in Taiwan as the Creative and Cultural parks.  However, looking back on the cultural policies in recent ten years, it is found in some cases that only construction revitalization and activity planning at one site were considered.  The link between industries adjacent to city and spatial structure was neglected which could not effectively integrate local resources and had a limited influence on urban development.  In addition, the lack of revision of related ordinances made it hard to successfully promote reuse program, so the art space could not fit in the life and culture of surrounding communities and was short of financial support for long.    This research first reviews references regarding definitions of cultural creative industry, the development and the relationship between its aggregation process and urban development in each nation to investigate the position and development goals of Taiwan’s Creative and Cultural Park.  Secondly, it studies the development of Taiwan cultural industry and analyzes the status survey to discuss issues on the parks, urban development and surrounding spaces.  Next, the research explores the relevant foreign cases collected, and further concludes what is worth of emulating for development of the Huashan Creative and Cultural Park.  Finally, it sums up the above as well as proposes development strategy and suggestion for urban space neighboring to the Huashan Creative and Cultural Park from the new perspective of urban space planning with the creative city, the urban cultural tourism and the cultural life cycle which focus on culture and creativity, to form a special urban culture and creative space as the basis for aggregation of the said industry which facilitates prosperity of urban industrial cluster and achieves continuous renovation and innovation.

